Fast-rising actress, Omobewaji oyediji aka Bewaji of Lagos has disagreed with individuals who clamour for the support of businesses owned by friends and associates. She recounted her disappointing experience in her attempt to support an associate’s business by ordering a hair. Bewaji of Lagos said this particular associate failed to deliver the hair she ordered despite her prior explanation that it was needed urgently for an important event.   I must marry virgin from Israel – Actor Aguba     10 Nigerian entertainers with traditional titles     Running mate: Funke Akindele unfit for leadership – Uche…   She added the incidence has further strengthened her resolve never to patronise any friend or associate-owned business but outsiders. “Everyone shouting about supporting your friends business! NOT me I literally missed an important event cos I ordered hair from someone I know! “And she didn’t deliver after telling n explaining how urgent n important it was for me to get my hair! I’d rather patronize an outsider,” she wrote.